Welcome to the future. With the super-subtle code name "Project Zero," this plane has it all. It's a tiltrotor, like the famous vertical-takeoff-and-landing V-22 Osprey. It's hybrid, like the the E-Star 2. Project Zero can be flown with a pilot on board or without. It looks almost completely alien. And it is only a technology demonstration, rather than the first of a new line of products.

Spearheaded by Augusta Westland, Project Zero involved collaborators in nine countries. It has a carbon graphite body, lacks hydraulic systems, and uses a hybrid diesel-electric engine, because electric alone just isn't powerful enough. Best of all, it was designed, built, and tested in 12 months.

The Italian-made HammerHead is Europe's largest drone. Following the path of the Firescout C, this massive turboprop is built on the body of a commercial airplane, one usually full of people. In this case, it started as a P.180 Avanti II, a plane known for its unusual forward wing. In aviation circles, that's known as a canard, but from where I sit, it looks like an airplane mustache.

Like America's iconic predator drones, the HammerHead is designed for reconnaissance but will be able to carry up to 500 pounds of payload, usually sensors like the built-in FLIR infrared camera but also optional weapons.

The distinctive feature about the HammerHead, perhaps its biggest selling point, is its variable speed. The Hammerhead can do normal drone stuff, cruising at 45,000 feet for up to 16 hours, cruising at the leisurely pace of 135 mph, much like a Predator. Predators, however, can't ever go much faster than their cruising speed, topping out about 20 mph above their norm. The HammerHead, on the other hand, can go almost 500 mph at maximum speed, which will put it in place quickly and let it run away from a tricky situation.
It's still a few years from entering regular service, but the HammerHead is a very clear sign that meaningful drone innovation isn't only happening on this side of the Atlantic.
Designed by European Aeronautic Defence and Space Company and Aero Composites Saintonge, the E-Fan is a two-seat training plane that's fully electric.

Lithium-polymer batteries are common in cellphones, but here, two much larger ones provide the power for the plane, giving it a maximum flight time of an hour. Improvements to flight time will come with improvements in battery life. Composite material construction makes the plane very light, which is how the plane can have a 31-foot-wide wingspan and 22-foot length and still have a weight less than half that of an average car.
Lightweight and small are what the first generations of all-electric planes will look like, but as batteries improve, expect planes like this to get much bigger.
The Diamond Aircraft DA36 E-Star 2 is basically a flying Prius. It debuted at the Paris Air Show in 2011, but was back this year for asecond-generation showcase.

Much like the all-electric E-Fan, the E-Star 2 (part of a collaboration between Siemens, the European Aeronautic Defence and Space Company, and Diamond Aircraft) is a small, light plane, with a large wingspan and modest fuselage. The similarity is no accident—when testing a new engine, especially one with lower power than fossil fuels provide, it's best to stick with a light, workable shape. Future designs can tackle more useful functions, like carrying multiple people or heavy cargo, once the engine is sorted.

The engine itself consists of a small rotary engine that takes fossil fuel, which in turn an electrical generator that feeds the actual electric engine driving the plane. There's also an on-board battery, which is recharged while the plane glides along at cruising altitude. So far, the plane has successfully flown for an hour.

对于最简单的模型，我们看看一个轮子的行为。
轮子在地面上滚动，如果我们现在刹车，轮子会转动变慢，但是可能不是立刻停止转动。这样的话，轮子的转动过的切线距离和车辆走过的路面距离可能不同。
下面的图中，红色的线段是车辆走过的距离。但是实际上轮子有一段滑动，所以实际上轮子转过的周长要小于车走过的距离，蓝色的线表示出二者的差异，而实际上轮子转过的周长是红色的减去蓝色的。
然后可以定义轮子的滑动 S 为 蓝色线段/红色线段。如果 S=1，那么说明轮子就完全在滑动，如果 S=0，说明轮子在完全滚动。
然后我们可以分析摩擦力跟 S 的关系了。
上图的右边，纵轴是摩擦系数，横轴是 S。
这样图给出的意思是说，如果轮子完全滚动，那么摩擦力很小，如果轮子完全滑动，摩擦力会大些，但是并不是最大，最大的摩擦力在两种极端情况之间。
我们刹车当然希望车辆快点停下来，所以我们当然希望刹车时摩擦力最大。那么就需要在刹车时保持车轮在完全停止转动和完全不滑动之间的某个合适的状态，这就是 ABS 的主要功能了。
）这门课程的第五课：Antilock Braking System 就是要解释为什么我们要 ABS，以及具体如何实现。

2、在某些不良路面，会加大刹车距离
